Train Model for GPS

Source: R/train_GPS.R
train_GPS.Rd

Estimate the conditional mean and sd of exposure level as a function of covariates with xgboost algorithm.

Usage

train_GPS(cov.mt, w.all)

Arguments

cov.mt

Covariate matrix containing all covariates. Each row is a sample and each column is a covariate.

w.all

A vector of observed exposure levels.

Value

A data.table that includes:

  • a vector of estimated GPS at the observed exposure levels;

  • a vector of estimated conditional means of exposure levels when the covariates are fixed at the observed values;

  • estimated standard deviation of exposure levels

Examples

mydata <- generate_synthetic_data()
GPS_m <- train_GPS(as.matrix(mydata[,c("cf1", "cf2", "cf3", "cf4",
                                          "cf5", "cf6")]),
                      as.matrix(mydata$treat))
